<p>Solar panel installations in Denver typically range from \$2.70 to \$3.20 per watt before incentives, with most residential systems falling between 5kW and 10kW depending on household energy consumption. The city's excellent solar irradiance allows for faster payback periods, typically 8-11 years, while systems can last 25-30 years. Denver's high altitude actually improves solar panel efficiency, as panels perform better in cooler temperatures despite the intense sunlight at 5,280 feet above sea level.</p>

